        "title": "No niin: one phrase, twenty meanings",
        "summary": "Finns joke that 'no niin' is the only phrase you really need - the tone does the rest. It opens meetings, serves dinner, scolds children, wraps up visits and recovers lost thoughts. Its cousins: jaaha (well well), jaahas (what's this then), selvä homma (all sorted).",
